commit.message: Merge branch 'py38' of https://github.com/jdufresne/tinycss2 into jdufresne-py38

Fix ResourceWarning due to unclosed file in test_tinycss2.py

Running the tests with warnings would previously result in the warning emitted:

    tinycss2/test_tinycss2.py:80
      .../tinycss2/tinycss2/test_tinycss2.py:80: ResourceWarning: unclosed file <_io.TextIOWrapper name='/home/jon/devel/tinycss2/tinycss2/css-parsing-tests/color3.json' mode='r' encoding='utf-8'>
        json_data = json.load(open(os.path.join(

To solve, open and close the file with a context manager. The directory
to the data is now calculated and cached once rather than in each call
of load_json().

Python 3 only cleanups

As the project is Python 3 only, can do a few cleanups:

- Remove __future__ imports
- Remove u prefix from strings
- Remove inheritance from object

All of the above are defaults in Python 3.

Add testing for Python 3.8

Python 3.8 was released on October 14th, 2019.

Raise a parse error when reaching EOF in strings and URLs

Fix #5.
Don't crash when ident token has no lowercase equivalent

Fix authorized "--" idents parsing

One more example of "we should blindly do what the spec asks us to do".

Rename test file

It is automatically found by pytest now.
